The National Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Prince Uche Secondus has felicitated with the Zamfara state Governor Alhaji Bello Matawalle on his victory at the Supreme Court on Friday, and urged him to be a good team leader. Prince Secondus reminded the governor and the party in the state that their victory came from God, adding that the governor and his team should appreciate that fact and work hard to make a lasting mark with the mandate. Secondus in a statement by his Media Aide, Ike Abonyi also advised the governor to unite the people and move quickly to tackle the myriad of challenges facing the state most of which steamed from bad governance witnessed in the state in the past. “God has designed this position for you for a purpose and you must do everything humanly possibly not to disappoint both the people and the almighty who sent you there. “Identify critical stakeholders who can help you achieve your goals and refuse to be intimidated because you have a special mandate from God,” Secondus said. Bayelsa verdict: PDP raises panel to reconcile with Jonathan, Wike, others Work with state governors to secure Nigeria, Secondus tells Buhari Work with state governors to secure Nigeria, Secondus tells Buhari